  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The shroud advertisement hereby permitted shall not be displayed until all the scaffold is in place and shall be removed when the scaffold is removed or within 7 months from the date of this consent, whichever is the\r\nsooner. This consent shall expire on [08/02/2024] and the advertisement hereby approved shall be removed and the land reinstated to its former condition by that date. \r\nReason: The advertisement is only acceptable for a limited period, having regard to the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy LP9 of the Wandsworth Local Plan (adopted July 2023) and the requirements of paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The area of the inset advertising shall not exceed 10.m x 2.5m and shall always form part of the larger shroud advertisement hereby permitted for the duration of the display. \r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy DMS8 and to comply with paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2019.",
    "Condition : 3 - No part of the shroud advertisement hereby permitted shall be illuminated.\r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the visual amenity of the area and neighbour residential amenity in accordance with Council policiesLP2 and LP9 of the Wandsworth Local Plan (adopted July 2023) and DMS1 and to comply with paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2019.\r\n"
  ],
